The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic detection of electricity theft using a multi-scale dense connected convolution neural network. This approach involves using deep learning techniques to capture long-term and short-term periodic features within the sequential data. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, since the proposed approach involves using convolutional neural networks, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper focuses on the detection of electricity theft, which is a practical application of machine learning, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible sub-category.
